wikipedia_page.main: Eboni Usoro-Brown (née Beckford-Chambers; born 4 February 1988) is an English netball player who currently plays for England and for Team Bath in the position of defender as well as the goal keeper. She attended Gordon's School in Surrey from 2001 to 2004. Usoro-Brown graduated from the University of Bristol with an LLB Law degree in 2009, before completing the LLM degree in 2010 at the same Law School. Usoro-Brown went on to complete the Legal Practice Course at the University of the West of England.
